            <trans-unit id="">
                <source>List of active Input Rules.
<br/>In order to activate a rule, it must first be mapped to a source language.
<br/>Once the content is found in the source language <b>and</b> an active output rule for the target language is defined, it will be protected as an internal tag <b>and</b> automatically converted according to the defined output rule.
<br/><b>Rules with higher priorities will be applied first.</b>
<br/>If the desired rule is not available in the drop-down list, activate it (or add and activate it) in the “Content Recognition Rules” tab.</source>
                <target></target>
            </trans-unit>
            <trans-unit id="">
                <source>List of active Output Rules.
<br/>Add rules here per <b>target language</b>. These rules work together with your active input rules to protect and convert content.
<br/>If the desired rule is not available in the drop-down list, activate it (or add and activate it) in the “Content Recognition Rules” tab.</source>
                <target></target>
            </trans-unit>
            <trans-unit id="">
                <source>List of predefined regular expressions that can be used to protect and/or convert content.
<br/>Or define your own rules.
<br/>Activate any rule you want to use as input or output here.
<br/>To find format-string rules, you can look at:
<br/><a href="https://icu4c-demos.unicode.org/icu-bin/locexp?d_=en#region" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">1. Locale related format presets</a>
<br/><a href="https://unicode-org.github.io/icu/userguide/format_parse/datetime/#datetime-format-syntax" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">2. Dates syntax</a>
<br/><a href="https://unicode.org/reports/tr35/tr35-numbers.html#Number_Format_Patterns" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">3. Number syntax</a>
<br/><a href="https://icu4c-demos.unicode.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">4. ICU Demonstration</a></source>
                <target></target>
            </trans-unit>
