            <trans-unit id="VGhlIExldmVuc2h0ZWluIGRpc3RhbmNlIGZvciBhIHNlZ21lbnQgd2l0aGluIGEgd29ya2Zsb3cgc3RlcCBpcyBjYWxjdWxhdGVkIGJldHdlZW4gdGhlIHNlZ21lbnTigJlzIHZlcnNpb24gYmVmb3JlIGl0IHdhcyBlZGl0ZWQgaW4gdGhhdCBzdGVwIGFuZCBpdHMgbGFzdCBlZGl0IHdpdGhpbiB0aGUgc2FtZSBzdGVwLg==">
                <source>The Levenshtein distance for a segment within a workflow step is calculated between the segment’s version before it was edited in that step and its last edit within the same step.</source>
                <target>La distance de Levenshtein au sein d’une étape de workflow pour un segment est calculée entre la version du segment avant le traitement dans une étape de workflow et la dernière modification dans l’étape de workflow.</target>
            </trans-unit>
            <trans-unit id="VGhlIExldmVuc2h0ZWluIGRpc3RhbmNlIGZyb20gdGhlIHN0YXJ0IG9mIHRoZSB3b3JrZmxvdyBmb3IgYSBzZWdtZW50IGlzIGNhbGN1bGF0ZWQgYmV0d2VlbiB0aGUgdmVyc2lvbiBvZiB0aGUgc2VnbWVudCBhdCB0aGUgc3RhcnQgb2YgdGhlIHdvcmtmbG93IGFuZCBpdHMgbGFzdCBleGlzdGluZyBlZGl0Lg==">
                <source>The Levenshtein distance from the start of the workflow for a segment is calculated between the version of the segment at the start of the workflow and its last existing edit.</source>
                <target>La distance de Levenshtein au début du workflow pour un segment est calculée entre la version du segment au début du workflow et sa dernière édition existante.</target>
            </trans-unit>
            <trans-unit id="">
                <source>The OpenID Connect implementation of translate5 makes it possible to assign a client on the IDP side to a client in translate5. The assignment is made via the client number. Further information can be found in the translate5 <a href="https://confluence.translate5.net/x/BgDgAw" target="_blank">documentation.</a></source>
                <target></target>
            </trans-unit>
