            <trans-unit id="">
                <source>This language resource is not yet connected to any other language resource.
<br/>Connections are created from source language resource to target one.
<br/>The language resource can only be connected to another language resource if the following conditions are met:
<br/>- Both language resources have the same language pair
<br/>- Both language resources are assigned to the same client
<br/>- Both language resources have data that can be synchronized, e.g: terms can be converted into a glossary
<br/>- The target language resource is not yet linked to the other language resource (at the moment we do not support multiple sources)
<br/>Synchronization always takes place in one direction: source data -&gt; target</source>
